article.headline: Monmouth 70, Wagner 63
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Marques Alston scored 16 points and Whitney Coleman keyed a second-half run to help Monmouth beat Wagner 70-63 on Thursday night. Trailing 47-39, Coleman hit a jumper to start a 24-5 run that gave Monmouth (11-3, 6-6 NEC) a 63-52 lead with 2 1/2 minutes left. Jamal Smith scored 21 points to lead Wagner (9-14, 6-6), which had won four of its last five games.
